  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7040.38 sitting directly between the massive +13.9B gamma wall at 7035 and +13.7B at 7050, dealers are in active hedging mode following the detected wall break and -3.6% 5-minute drop. In this PIN regime, dealers will aggressively buy this dip as they're long gamma below current levels, creating strong support around the 7035 max positive gamma strike. The thick positive gamma cluster from 7000-7100 should contain price action and promote mean reversion, with dealers selling any bounces back toward 7050-7100 resistance.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 7050 as dealers buy the dip around current levels.",
